= The Abdication of the Dean

The Dean has been convinced that his abdication is the only way to save Russia from civil war, and thus has abdicated in favor of his brother, Prof. Dr. Habilitated Michael. However, Prof. Dr. Habilitated Michael also sees the position as Dean to be untenable, and thus has refused to take the position

Now, the reign of the Dean is over, and power is vested in the Provisional Government.
@petrograd_soviet
title: The Students' Council
view-if: ps_seen < n_players
go-to: intro_menu
on-arrival: ps_seen += 1

= The Students' Council

The FAIS Students' Council is an elected council comprised of representatives of students and computer science students throughout the faculty. Organized in the wake of the general strike and the breakdown of the established order, it harkens back to the FAIS Students' Council of 2021, which functioned as an alternative government in the faculty during the Pandemic.

The leaders of the Council, mostly SMP and NKF intellectuals, have organized an Executive Committee, and elected the Semp Nikolai Chkheidze as the chairman. They see its goal as ending the general strike and advocating for the students and computer science students, acting as a watchdog over the bourgeois Provisional Government. They command the students and computer science students to go back to work, and to obey the Provisional Government insofar as it does not disobey the directives of the Council.


