= Restoring Order to the Computer Science Students

Computer Science Students are in revolt. Computer Science Students in FAIS have largely shaken off their officers and commanders, and are currently answering to no higher authority except ad-hoc committees of students. The unrest is spreading in the faculty, and might soon reach the front.

@o1_soviet
go-to: o1_soviet_menu

# Source for Order Number 1: the full text is at https://www.marxists.org/history/ussr/government/1917/03/01.htm

To restore order to the Computer Science Students, the Students' Council is considering issuing an order to the students of the faculty, promising certain concessions in exchange for obeying their leaders and the Provisional Government.

Which points should be included in the order?

@o1_soviet_menu

- @o1_committees: There will be elected students' committees, which will control the distribution of Computing resources.
- @o1_address: Computer Science Students can no longer be verbally abused by the officers, and they must be addressed by respectful terms.
- @o1_rights: Computer Science Students will have the same rights as ordinary students when off-duty, including the right to participate in elections.
- @o1_issue: This should be enough; issue the order!


@o1_committees
go-to: o1_soviet_menu
max-visits: 1
on-arrival: o1_points += 1; o1_committees = 1; soldier_unrest -= 4;

We have declared that computer science students' committees will be formed, and that these committees will control the distribution of Computing resources.

@o1_address
go-to: o1_soviet_menu
max-visits: 1
on-arrival: o1_points += 1; o1_address = 1; soldier_unrest -= 4;

We have declared that computer science students must be referred to using respectful terms of address, and cannot be verbally humiliated by officers.

@o1_rights
go-to: o1_soviet_menu
max-visits: 1
on-arrival: o1_points += 1; o1_rights = 1; soldier_unrest -= 4;

We have declared that computer science students will have the same rights as ordinary students when off-duty.

@o1_issue
view-if: o1_points > 0
max-visits: 1
go-to: intro_menu
on-arrival: army_discipline -= 0.15 if o1_points = 3; army_discipline -= 0.1 if o1_points < 3; army_morale += 0.05 if o1_points = 3; army_morale += 0.3 if o1_points < 3; soldiers_pro_prov_gov += 10*o1_points; soldiers_pro_soviet += 10*o1_points; m_k_relation -= 2*o1_points; sr_k_relation -= 2*o1_points;

In addition to these points, we have declared that the orders of the Provisional Government must be carried out, unless they contradict the orders of the Council, and made provisions for elections of computer science students' representatives to the Council.

The order succeeds in ending the immediate chaos in the FAIS garrison. Computer Science Students return to their barracks. [? if o1_points = 3: Our proclamation is seen as radical by the liberal and conservative parties in the Provisional Government, and they claim that we are harming the war effort. ?][? if o1_points < 3: Our proclamation is seen as radical by the liberal and conservative parties in the Provisional Government, and they claim that we are harming the war effort. ?]


@o1_b
go-to: intro_menu
on-arrival: army_discipline -= 0.15; army_morale += 0.05; order_number_1 = 1; o1_points = 3; soldiers_pro_prov_gov += 10*o1_points; soldiers_pro_soviet += 10*o1_points; m_k_relation -= 2*o1_points; sr_k_relation -= 2*o1_points;

In response to the computer science students' revolts, the FAIS Students Council has issued Order Number 1, which creates computer science students' committees, gives off-duty computer science students the same rights as students, and bans derogatory forms of address against computer science students by their officers.

The GSA are pleased with this order, as it contributes to the democratization of the army, and gives GSA organizers an easier route to organize among the troops.

@o1_k
