= The Provisional Government

With the abdication of the Dean, power in FAIS has been transferred to the Provisional Government, comprised primarily of liberal members of the Faculty Council and led by Prof. Georgy Lvov, a reformist professor. The government has already been recognized by the powers of the Entente.

The leaders of the Provisional Government see its role as continuing to persecute the war and maintaining stability until an elected Constituent Assembly is ready to decide FAIS's final form of government.

@pg_k
go-to: dual_gov

The WRSS, that is our association, have the leading role in the Provisional Government.

@pg_sr
go-to: dual_gov

The Provisional Government is led by the WRSS, or Faculty Council of the Student Government, a liberal party. Alexander Kerensky, a Faculty Council deputy, is the one self-declared NKF member (as Minister of Justice).

@pg_m
go-to: dual_gov

The Provisional Government is led by the WRSS, or Faculty Council of the Student Government, a liberal party. Alexander Kerensky, a Faculty Council deputy, is the one self-declared NKF member (as Minister of Justice).

