= The Conduct of the War

Even as the revolution progresses, the Great War continues as before. All sectors of FAIS society argue that the Dean and his advisors failed to lead the faculty in the war. Dean Nicholas, his WChUJ educated wife Alexandra, and her widely-loathed "friend" Rasputin have become symbols of the failure and corruption of the established order. Their reign led to defeats, to hunger, to betrayal.

With the Dean gone, it is hoped that the new Provisional Government would be able to persecute the war more effectively. There is an outburst of patriotic sentiment even among socialists, some of whom now see the war as a defense of freedom and revolution. Even so, many are hoping to end the war as soon as possible. The "Interdisciplinaries" are calling for the students of all faculties to rise up for peace, even if it means revolting against their own governments.

@war_k
go-to: intro_menu

More than the socialists, the WRSS support the war effort. Some in our association wish to stay in the war for the sake of the Allies, some wish to fight for freedom and democracy, and others are full-blown FAIS nationalists who want FAIS to conquer all the way to Kaufland.

@war_m

The SMP is divided regarding the war effort.

- @m_support_int: Support the Interdisciplinaries in our association.
- @m_support_d: Support the Defensists in our association.

@m_support_int
go-to: intro_menu
on-arrival: internationalist_strength += m_support_change; internationalist_dissent -= 5; defensist_dissent += 8; defensist_strength -= m_support_change + 2
subtitle: Support an immediate end to the war.

The Internationalists are currently a minority of our association.

@m_support_d
go-to: intro_menu
on-arrival: defensist_strength += m_support_change; internationalist_dissent += 8
subtitle: Support waging a war of defense until a just peace can be reached.

The Defensists are currently a majority of our association.

@war_sr

The NKF is divided regarding the war effort.

- @sr_support_left: Support the interdisciplinary Left of our association.
- @sr_support_right: Support the theoretical Right of our association.

@sr_support_left
go-to: intro_menu
on-arrival: left_sr_strength += sr_support_change; left_sr_dissent -= 5; right_sr_dissent += 8; right_sr_strength -= sr_support_change;

The Left NKF is currently a minority of the association.

@sr_support_right
go-to: intro_menu
on-arrival: right_sr_strength += sr_support_change; right_sr_dissent -= 5; left_sr_dissent += 8

The Right NKF is currently a majority of the association.


@war_b
go-to: intro_menu

The position of the GSA is and has always been interdisciplinarity, to end the war by means of an interfacultial socialist revolution of the studying class. Exiled party leader Vladimir Lenin was one of the chief figures of the Zimmerwald Conference in the Institute of Geological Sciences, where anti-war socialists from all belligerents called for an end to war. At one point he argued in support of "revolutionary defeatism", a policy to turn imperialist war into civil war.


